BACKGROUND:

We were informed by the applicant that the above material is to be exported to as per packing list. We had inspected all the 80 Nos. HDPE Drums were found the same to be new, sound and intact.

PACKING:

The material was packed in 80 Nos. HDPE Drums mouth opened with cap facilities.

All 80 Nos. HDPE Drums Drums were found externally sound and intact condition.

SURVEY:

We had inspected below given container prior to its stuffing and the same was found clean and fit for stuffing. All the above 80 Nos. HDPE Drums were stuffed into the container on 17TH April, 2024.

CONCLUSION:

  • All HDPE Drums were found externally sound and intact condition
  • Total 80 Nos. were Palletized using CP9 Pine Wood to provide cargo stabilizes and wrapped to avoid dust and dirt.
  • All 80 Nos. were palletized as 20 pallets were made out for 80 Drums.
  • Lashing was done at last with cord strap along the rings/hooks to prevent movement inside the

Container.

  • The lashing was found to be adequate and satisfactory.

The above are our findings at the time and place of inspection and it does not relieve the concerned parties from their contractual obligations.
